I.    Introduction

A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Ajinomoto Windsor, Inc. facility located at 301 West Third Street in Toluca, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This RMP includes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 

?    Introduction;

?    AjinomotoWindsor, Inc. policies to protect health, environment, and safety;

?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;

?    Hazard Assessment;

?    Prevention Program;

?    Five-Year Accident History;

?    Emergency Response Plan; 

?    Emergency Communications;

?    Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;

?    Planned changes to improve safety; and

?    Management Program



II.    Ajinomoto Windsor, Inc. Policies To Protect Health, Environment, and Safety

Risk management and safety are important concerns at Ajinomoto Windsor, Inc.; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Ajinomoto Windsor, Inc. is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Ajinomoto Windsor, Inc.'s policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.



